<br>
If you wish to hide in the bushes with the other softskins then by all means do so ... and when my claws rend the flesh of the defiant, your traitorish scales will not be spared.<br>
<br>
- Falzure<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
/peer<br>
<br>
Err, perhaps you're confusing Skathris Ven'Sho with some other guild. To my knowledge we're the ONLY Iksar-only guild that won't have ANYTHING to do with softskins. We hate all softskins. On very rare ocassion one of us might group with one for some particular need (in 39 levels Voskor never has), but we never ever trust them or count them as equals.<br>
<br>
And &quot;Patriarch&quot; is the cultural term for beastlords. Just as shamans are Mystics and monks are Swifttails.<br>
<br>
I realize your post was a joke but I wanted to make sure you had your facts straight before you go in-game and start RPing like we're traitors or something. To the contrary, we RP as rabid patriots. Iksar above all, for the glory of Cabilis and all of that.<br>
<br>
And /bonk Kelisk, Iksar rangers would NOT make sense. They're not into that nature shiz. Also, rangers are most commonly portrayed as loner types, which doesn't fit the Iksar mold. If they wanted to give Iksar access to tracking, they'd be better off giving it to beastlords. A /pet track command would actually be really cool - you pick the tracking target, and your pet takes off running toward the target, and you have to follow the pet, taking into account all the bizarre pathing and pet aggro and everything else. Hee.<br>
<br>
Ok, I'm done, put the train back on the tracks now. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Voskor Oth<br>
Legionnaire of Cabilis (and yes I did all my pike quests dammit) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udvara.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dvara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/15/02 3:36:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1537.topic&index=42>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.grimtidings.net/chosen/dvaraphoto.jpg height=108 width=108></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> Seems to me that an Iskar, being more of a primal creature would have the ability to track. Most reptilian species have a superior sense of smell, &lt;especially flesh and meat&gt; and the uncanny knack of sensing heat sources ie: warm rocks, living creatures. Vipers actually hunt by sensing heat given off by creatures. I think all Iskar should track!<br>
<br>
Dvara <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Iksar Fanatic</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/15/02 4:58:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1537.topic&index=43>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions</span><hr size=1> I'd love that as well Dvara, and I think it'd make great sense for Iksar to all have an innate ability to track.<br>
<br>
