<br>
Also, there is an obvious grouping of Scaled evils, the Biggies in the swamps and DE's (not necessarily together but amongst their own).  <br>
<br>
But what about the evil human, erudite and gnome bretheren?  Do they try to form a parntership amongst themselves?  I would be interested to hear?  That alliance would give them quite a bit of safe area to hunt in.  I guess if a bard does (can on this server) chose RZ as a deity, they would be evil and thus your tracker.<br>
<br>
Still, no safe spot for them to use a soul binder in Qeynos area? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usmallcutepuppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/15/02 5:59:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1537.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Questions still...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> /boggle I assume you are not referring to Swifttails when you make this comment, as most Grand Master Iksar ARE loners.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
True, I wasn't thinking about that, and that's a good point. Sartar (sp) the Unrivaled tells a pretty good story about his loner-ness. But still, I don't see the Swifttails as being a separate entity from Cabilis. They're still very much integrated into the society. <br>
<br>
I guess I'm just hung up on the image of Aragorn (the consummate ranger) being sort of off by himself all the time, affiliated only with the other Rangers, and viewed apprehensively by &quot;civilized&quot; society. I can't see an Iksar in that role. Of course there are many types and degrees of rangers too, but the image that first comes to MY mind when I think &quot;ranger&quot; doesn't fit an Iksar at all.<br>
<br>
At any rate, we agree that they're still not into that nature shiz. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
But I still don't see where a Swifttail who needed help from a blueskin to get his Whistling Fists gets off mocking Kelisk for wishing that Iksar could track. /tease <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 246<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/15/02 6:02:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1537.topic&index=48>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lunarpages.com/maladominus/exhibit/trollfood.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Beastlords should have tracking in the first place</span><hr size=1> If Iksar really need tracking, then my proposal makes the best sense: <br>
<br>
**** Give Beastlords the tracking capability <br>
<br>
#1) Iksar already have Beastlords<br>
<br>
#2) Tracking makes a LOT of sense on a Beastlord<br>
<br>
#3) Beastlords are the &quot;king of the animals&quot;....Beastlords are the &quot;king of the jungle&quot; (e.g. Tarzan) so why the hell not be able to track wild creatures, eh? <br>
<br>
#4) This line of reasoning eliminates the need for the silly concept of Iksar Ranger-nature-boys and how some nature-loving tree hugger Karana-loving Ranger freak is now some evil Cazic-Thule worshipping lizard with a lisp. I'm sure this is one of the major reasons why Verant will hesitate to even bother with the idea of an Iksar Ranger... it's simply too hard for Verant to justify it in the presence of current EQ lore, trends and history. <br>
<br>
#5) Beastlord tracking.... makes the PERFECT sense, since NOT only does it enable tracking on the leezard race, but it also enables it on a couple of other &quot;dark&quot; races as well (e.g. Trollies, Ogres).  Thus you are killing three birds with one stone. <br>
<br>
Enough said. <br>
<br>
<br>
